<TITLE> Govt exempts media from curfew </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, August 23 (bdnews24.com)All newspapers, news agencies, radio and television channels were exempted from the curfew, the Press Information Department said in a statement Thursday. PID-issued accreditation cards or ID cards issued by their own organisations would serve as curfew passes for media personnel including journalists and technical hands could use, the handout said. It also said the vehicles transporting the newspaper and TV journalists and technicians will also be exempted from the curfew. Despite assurances by the government, harassment of journalists by army personnel has been reported through the city. Various media organisations say their journalists and technical staff have been beaten or otherwise roughly treated by army personnel despite showing accredited IDs and travelling in clearly marked press vehicles. bdn
